This paper presents a deterministic distributed algorithm for edge coloring in the LOCAL model, which is a well-studied problem in distributed computing. The algorithm improves upon previous results and uses novel techniques to achieve a better bound on the number of colors used. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The problem of edge coloring is also related to graph theory, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also likely sub-categories. The algorithm involves communication and coordination among nodes, so cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses techniques such as matching and packing, which are common in algorithms research, so cs.AL (Computational Complexity) is also a possible sub-category.
